# System-wide KWin defaults for Emryk Workstation (KConfig cascade: a user's
# ~/.config/kwinrc overrides anything here, so these are defaults, not policy).
#
# InputMethod: explicitly empty. Plasma 6.6 ships plasma-keyboard (Maliit's
# replacement) as the compiled-in default virtual keyboard and it auto-raises
# at the greeter and on first login — wrong default for a non-touch ML
# workstation. An explicitly-empty value beats the compiled-in default; an
# absent key would not. Re-enable per user via System Settings > Keyboard >
# Virtual Keyboard (writes to ~/.config/kwinrc, this file stays untouched).
[Wayland]
InputMethod=
